<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>The Premier League have confirmed four new positive coronavirus results have been returned from the 2,131 players and club staff tested between September 7-13.</p>

<p>Those who have tested positive will now have to self-isolate for a period of ten days.</p>

<p>It was revealed that just three positive results were recorded in the first round of top-flight testing last week.    </p>

<p>The Premier League have confirmed four new positive coronavirus results from the new round</p>

<p>The identities of those who have contracted the disease will not be made public by the league due to medical confidentiality reasons.</p>

<p>Manchester City confirmed that Riyad Mahrez and Aymeric Laporte were two of the individuals to have tested positive from last week's batch of testing. </p>

<p>Both players have been forced to undergo a period of quarantine, and the club revealed that neither were showing any symptoms of the virus.</p>

<p>More to follow. </p>
